    public class Allele<G extends Gene>
extends PrototypeBase

    Base class for representations of alleles within a Genotype. Alleles represent the mutable aspect of Genes and as such generally contain values that may be altered by a Mutator or Recombiner.

    Sub-classes must implement a copy-constructor that accepts a single parameter which is the allele to copy, and which should generally just call super() with the allele to copy. See com.ojcoleman.europa.configurable.PrototypeBase#Prototype(PrototypeBase).

    Note that an Allele belongs to a specific Genotype, but may share the same Gene as Alleles in other Genotypes. Alleles and Genotypes directly reference one another, but a Gene is only referenced by Alleles. A given Gene should only be included once in a Genotype.

    Author:
    O. J. Coleman
